                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2607</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Reinsch</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-13T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 13, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your June 12, 8 p.m. The Department on June 5, 9 and 12, telegraphed the Embassy
                    at Tokyo making denials and corrections of certain false statements appearing in
                    Japanese newspapers similar to those which you mention. Department assumes that
                    you have taken steps to nullify effects of false statements circulated in
                    Peking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
